 to participate in the exchange), a stable equilibrium would allow consumers
 to spread their long-term assets.
 If for example, we randomly select winners and losers in every band and
 swap them for a certain cost, the consumers woud give up more as by losing
 their current band as they move up the income band.
 At the same time, less income does not necessarily shun the consumer to
 the lowest bands due the possibility of being randomly selected for being
 promoted to a higher band as a winner.
 
\end_layout

